{
  "doc_id": "17416",
  "text": "Hippocampal neurons were analyzed by in situ hybridization as described previously [CITATION_1] . In situ hybridization on free-floating, 40-mm coronal brain sections cut at the level of dorsal hippocampus was performed as described previously [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Probe specificity for the CDS or for exon 4 or 6 was demonstrated previously [CITATION_4] . Hybridization was followed by high stringency washes with 0.01 Â sodium saline citrate buffer containing 0.1% Tween-20 (SSCT) at 60 1C. All in situ hybridizations on brain sections from treated animals were conducted in contemporary with brain sections from control animals. The use of non-radioactive in situ hybridization using digoxigeninlabeled probes for semiquantitative evaluation of the in situ staining has been previously validated by us and other laboratories [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] .",
